						<p>Gift of 12 <hi rend="italic">paṇams</hi> by Piḷḷaiyappaṉ of Pāriyūr, a <hi rend="italic">veḷḷāḷa</hi> from Kāñchikkūval-nāḍu to the temple of Amaraviṭaṅkap Pe[rumāḷ] for probably conducting the early morning awakening <hi rend="italic">(paḷḷieḻuchchi)</hi> ceremony of the deity. Three <hi rend="italic">śiva-brāhmaṇas</hi> of the temple agreed to maintain the grant.</p>						

